# Register the observer brain as a wiki root

## Step

Resolved when `joelclaw-observer`'s `.brain` is an entry in
`dark-wizard/brain-roots.json` (name `observer`, following the registry's
stated onboarding model: one entry, crawls audit but never define), the
dark-wizard change is committed and pushed (fleet rule), and a local wiki
build proves observer pages appear in the catalog without breaking anything
(privacy exclusions still apply). Joel's call, 2026-07-17.

## Result (2026-07-17)

Registered. `dark-wizard/brain-roots.json` now carries an `observer` entry
(repo `joelhooks/joelclaw-observer`, brainPath `.brain`), committed and
pushed as dark-wizard `e03b805`. Pre-flight: the observer brain is 23
committed `.svx` files (tasks + index; areas/projects/resources/archives
present, no `.md` stragglers, no sensitive sections). Catalog proof: running
the wiki's `loadBrainPages()` against the updated registry yields
`{"user":695,"joelclaw":259,"observer":23,"wiki":67}` with observer keys like
`observer/tasks/neat-memory-beat` — no errors, existing roots unchanged. The
pages go live on the next wiki build ([Publish, Verify,
DM](./publish-verify-dm.svx) owns that).
